All of the above is good advice, but let me add to it.  Don't snare right away, wait till the mob is under 50% or maybe even 30% or 20%.  Snaring something while the melees have it engaged isn't going to help much, you just want to make sure it is snared before it starts running.

There are exceptions of course.  If you are kiting, then you obiously want to snare it asap.  But you said people were getting hit, which doesn't happen much if you are kiting, so I doubt that's your tactic.  

If the casters are always getting agro, an early snare could help.  The main tank will have a more time to taunt before it gets to the caster.

And let me stress it again...do *not* taunt unless you *want* to get hit.  That's all it is good for.  If you are trying to get a mob off a caster, taunt away.  But if the mob is already on the group's tank, let him do all the taunting.



-- C.

Also, you never say where "here" is that you are getting crappy XP.  PC maybe?  If so then yes, time to move to a new zone.  Try Marus Seru, or HHP/HHK, and maybe even Dawnshroud Peaks in another few levels.

And you never mentioned what equipment you currently have, so we can't easily suggest upgrades.  Off the top of my head, for 2hs, Weighty Polearms have been pretty cheap lately and have a good ratio.  For 1hs ... the only thing that comes to mind is centi shortsword, but I think they are a few hundred.

You have "most of the major armor peices?"  Does that mean you have slots with no armor?  If so, then I'd make that your number one priority.  Fill in missing slots before upgrading existing armor.


Best of luck, and enjoy being a ranger!


